Reminder Notice sent to Defendant has been returned.  Return to Sender.  Not Deliverable as Addressed.  Unable to Forward.

1:36 p.m.  Defendant present in court without counsel.  Andrew Christenson for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant confirms receipt of the criminal complaint and waives reading.  Court instructs the defendant of the maximum penalty on each count.  Court finds probable cause.  Court advises regarding DNA and expungement.  Court instructs the defendant of his right to an attorney.  Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  DA recites agreement, upon plea to the charge, will recommend a fine plus costs.  Defendant concurs, will accept.  Court goes over right to counsel.  Defendant waives right to counsel.  Court accepts waiver.

Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation. 

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty to count 1 as charged.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  Sentencing statement by DA.  No statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to:  $100 fine plus court costs.  Court grants the defendant 60 days to pay or payment plan.

Defendant is to complete processing with the Green Lake County Sheriff's Department.

Court adjourned at 1:41 p.m.
